HEADWORD: Arrearage
<hw>Ar*rear"age</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>arr⟦eacute⟧rage</ets>, fr. <ets>arri⟦egrave⟧re</ets>, OF.
<ets>arere</ets>. See <er>Arrear</er>.]</ety> <def>That which remains
unpaid and overdue, after payment of a part; arrears.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

